sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Returns the specified subnetwork.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Region - Name of the region.
  • Subnetwork - Name of the subnetwork.

Outputs:

  • Subnetwork - Subetwork is an object containing Name,ID,Creation Time Stamp,Network,IP Cidr Range,Gateway Address,Region,Self Link,Private IP Google Access,Finger Print,Purpose,Kind.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Virtual Private Network, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Requested subnetwork is doesn't exist.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Virtual Private Cloud connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Virtual Private Cloud Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
